                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in pencil by a modern hand: <quote>223 bl</quote>,<quote> 217 ?</quote>; left edge, in pencil by a modern hand:<quote> A 198</quote>; in ink by a medieval hand: <quote>liber sancti petri in Erfordia</quote>; <quote>P 47</quote> (repeated on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>); <quote>In hoc libello continentur subsignata</quote> followed by a table of contents; below, one line of erased text (perhaps owner's signature), 3 lines of text in Latin (partially illegible). </note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in ink by a medieval hand:<quote> Liber Sanctorum Pewtri et pauli in erfordia</quote>; below: <quote>hermannus markreffe est nomen meum </quote>(beneath these two lines are 7 lines of erased, but partially legible text); centre page, in ink by a medieval hand: 22 lines of text beginning <quote>Ex peccato originali relinquantur</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="L1v" to="L1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in ink by a medieval hand: Assit ??? (partially erased); below, in ink by a modern hand: <quote>Till Kongl. Bibliotheket inköpt från G. Stephens 23/10 1848.</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 3 double raised bands and endbands. Orignally, one clasp with brass catchplate. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in ink: <quote>4.</quote>; traces of a removed label; stamped in gold: <quote>A 198</quote>. </p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding" resp="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100380">
                                        <height quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="120" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="55" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Complex tooling consisting of tripple-line frames filled with stamped motifs, such as flowers and fleur-de-lis. </p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Leather worn and darkened. Clasp missing. Pastedown on <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>missing, board attachment visible. <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>, signs of repair at upper left corner. </condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
