                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100104">Germany</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100224">Erfurt</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate when="1460">1460</origDate>. The manuscript carries contemporary owner's signatures and what may be shelfmark from the <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100220">monastery of St Peter and Paul </placeName>in Erfurt (<locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>, <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/>; <quote>P47</quote> on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>). In addition, on <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/> a pesonal name is listed as a potential owner: <quote>hermannus markreffe</quote>. The text on <locus from="22r" to="37v" scheme="folios"/> has been provided with a colophon that states that the book was written in <date when="1460"/> by a <quote>confrater Wernherus</quote> for <quote>dominus Guntherus, alumnus claustri erforrdensis</quote>. </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Provenance unknown, but like the other <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100224">Erfurt</placeName> manuscripts in the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National LIbrary</orgName>'s collection it is likely that the manuscript remained in the monastery unitl its dissolution, when it would have bought by a private book dealer or collector from whom it was acquired by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/101069">George Stephens</persName>. </p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Purchased by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Librar</orgName>y from <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/101069">George Stephens</persName> in 30 Oct., <date when="1848"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
